Firstly install minikube in your local machine
The main purpose of installing minikube is to use Master Node and Worker nodes in same machine.
minikube is local Kubernetes, focusing on making it easy to learn and develop for Kubernetes.
What youâ€™ll need ::: 
2 CPUs or more
2GB of free memory
20GB of free disk space
Internet connection
Container or virtual machine manager

For installing in windows :: use the following command in command line to install MINIKUBE(K8s)  ::: winget install minikube 

check in command prompt ;; From a terminal with administrator access (but not logged in as root), run: minikube start

if minikube fails to start then check installing container or VM ,Mostly install docker ;;; docker --- VM + Container and easy to use in local machine 

TO INSTALL DOCKER :: https://hub.docker.com/search?q=&type=edition&offering=community&sort=updated_at&order=desc

after installing docker in local machine ,,,

Start a cluster using the docker driver:::: minikube start --driver=docker

To make docker the default driver: minikube config set driver docker

